      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Support managed Skill Workshop updates",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- allow Skill Workshop update/revise/apply flows for writable `openclaw-managed` skills under the user's OpenClaw skills directory\n- keep workspace skill support intact while preserving boundary checks for targets outside workspace/managed skills\n- update agent prompt, CLI copy, and docs from workspace-only language to writable user-owned skills\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: Skill Workshop previously rejected shared `openclaw-managed` skills even when they lived in the user's writable `~/.openclaw/skills` directory, forcing approved internal skill changes back to manual governed edits.\n- Real environment tested: Moeed's local OpenClaw installation on macOS, running the installed Skill Workshop path with shared managed skills under `~/.openclaw/skills`.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: Applied the installed-runtime equivalent of this source patch, then used Skill Workshop to update and apply shared managed skills (`skill-workshop`, `skill-creator`, `governance`, `improve`, and `scripting`), inspected the applied proposal, and checked live skill visibility with `openclaw skills info skill-workshop --agent openclaw`.\n- Evidence after fix: Terminal output copied from the live OpenClaw setup:\n\n```text\n$ skill_workshop list status=applied query=managed limit=5\n- improve-20260613-3fc2318e10 [applied, update, clean] improve: Update improve\n- governance-20260613-e5af96043e [applied, update, clean] governance: Update governance\n- skill-creator-20260613-fad38556bb [applied, update, clean] skill-creator: Update skill-creator\n- skill-workshop-20260613-0ba4a074dc [applied, update, clean] skill-workshop: Update skill-workshop\n- scripting-20260613-8e14e11f68 [applied, update, clean] scripting: Update scripting\n\n$ skill_workshop inspect proposal_id=skill-workshop-20260613-0ba4a074dc\nProposal: skill-workshop-20260613-0ba4a074dc\nStatus: applied\nKind: update\nSkill: skill-workshop\nVersion: v1\nScan: clean\n\n$ openclaw skills info skill-workshop --agent openclaw\nskill-workshop ✓ Ready\n\nSkill Workshop lifecycle discipline.\n\nDetails:\n  Source: openclaw-managed\n  Path: ~/.openclaw/skills/skill-workshop/SKILL.md\n  Visible to model: yes\n  Available as command: yes\n```\n\n- Observed result after fix: Shared managed skill updates no longer stop at `openclaw-managed` as read-only; approved updates can be proposed, scanned clean, applied, inspected as `applied`, and read back as live managed skills.\n- What was not tested: Upstream release installation after merge; the current proof is from the locally patched installed runtime plus this source branch's focused unit/type/lint/doc checks.\n- Proof limitations or environment constraints: The live environment contains the same behaviour as a local installed-runtime hotfix while this PR carries the source change upstream; the hotfix remains tracked locally until an upstream release includes equivalent behaviour.\n\n## Tests\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/skills/workshop/service.test.ts`\n- `pnpm tsgo:core`\n- `pnpm tsgo:core:test`\n- `pnpm lint:core`\n- `pnpm format:docs:check`\n- `git diff --check`",
        "branch": "fix/skill-workshop-managed-autonomy",
